<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100240317856352></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100240317856352><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=1933&mid=100240317856352>Info on the quest</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=1933&mid=100240317856352#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=107244><span id= >Venil</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>7 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Oct 6th 5:19 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings all, <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;   today I figured since I had the cash, I'd give this quest a try (on Zebuxoruk, price I saw was 4kpp for this earring).  I bought a stack of ruby for 2635pp (with 185 charisma) and headed to the swamp.  She wasn't on track at the time I arrived, so I kill a few of the humans and high elves wandering around (bad faction hits here).  She spawned near the entrance to guk after around an hour, so I set my plan in action.  being an enchanter, I reclaimed my pet, then charmed her and ran to the troll dealer in the middle of the zone.  By bringing her there, you can sell the lore hammer and axe as soon as you get them and reclaim 75pp of the initial 130pp for the rubies.  Eventually my charm broke off and she attacked me.  <br><br>First piece of good info :<br>She cons green at 49 and dual hits for 80 tops whith around 585 ac.<br><br>     Anyways, I charmed her again and gave her the rest of the rubies.  I went thru my whole stack and didn't get the earring, and I also noticed something else.<br><br>Second piece of info:<br>Once in a while, you get NOTHING for handing in the rubies (around 1 out of 8 times for me).<br><br>    At this point, I had gotten back 1400pp from selling the weapons, so I ran to Oggok to buy 10 more rubies.<br><br>Third piece of info:<br>There's nowhere to buy rubies in Oggok =)<br><br>     I got a friend to check on the web for the closest place to buy some, and it turns out it's in Grobb.  That's not great if you're KOS, but I had no problems being an enchanter.  This took me around 30 minutes, and when I came back, Lynuga was still there.  This time, I figured screw it, I gave her all the rubies and let the weapons drop on the ground.  I finally got my earring on the 24th ruby I handed in.<br><br>     Since I was done and there was no one else in the zone, I figured may as well kill, so I did.  <br><br>Final piece of info:<br>She has around 800-1200 hp and dropped 1 ruby and one quest ruby needed for the jeweled skull quest.<br><br>     Overall, this quest may be annoying and seem like a huge gamble, but the way I see it, I started with 2635 pp and ended up with one earring worth 4kpp+ and around 500pp so it was well worth it.<br><br>    Hope this has been some help because this wasn't the first time I tried the quest, and I know that without any info, it's a pain in the ass.<br><br>Venil<br>49 Enchanter<br>Zebuxoruk<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Kirith, 1st level Beastlord -- <br>Venil Arkenstone,<br>51st level Illusionist, Zebuxoruk</td></tr>
